It would be nice to have a set of language packs (en-br, en-us, fr, de, es, etc.) available for each version of confluence (us translation at http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DISC/English_US+Translation+%28final%29 is out of date for v2.5.4 and was updated < 1 mo. ago).

Also, currently it seems there is no way to "layer" customer-specific language changes atop the language plugin messages. So for example, we could change all references of Confluence to DukeWiki without having to merge the newer language pack properties in with our own. But the latter would just be a "nice to have".

